<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        No Floor Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Disables the ground floor and makes only building rooftops walkable, creating a rooftop-only environment.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What No Floor Event Points Do
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        A <Bold>No Floor</Bold> Event Point removes the walkable ground floor from the mission area,
        making only the top surfaces of buildings (rooftops) walkable. When active, the player and NPCs
        cannot walk on the normal street-level ground — they must stay on rooftops or fall through the
        missing floor.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This creates a rooftop-only environment, typically used in special mission scenarios where the
        ground is meant to be a hazard or void. No Floor is extremely rare — only <Bold>2</Bold>
        instances exist across all 76 retail missions, both in finale missions where the final boss
        battle takes place on rooftops.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Practical meaning:</Run>
                <Run> Place a No Floor Event Point in the mission to disable the ground floor. The floor disappears, and only building rooftops remain walkable. This is typically used at mission start with a None trigger.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        No Floor uses the standard Event Point common properties: index number, Event Point type,
        letter group, colour, position, facing direction, trigger settings, and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The index number and Event Point type are automatic. <Bold>Position</Bold> defines where the
        no-floor effect is centered or applied, though the exact spatial radius or scope is determined
        by the game engine. Colour and letter group are usually not critical for No Floor.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Position
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Position places the No Floor Event Point in the mission area. In retail missions, the Event
        Point is placed centrally in the rooftop battle area. The position may define the center of
        the no-floor effect or simply mark where the feature is active.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Y Altitude
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Y altitude should be set to a level that makes sense for the rooftop environment. In retail
        examples, it is set to rooftop height (Y: 1792), indicating the floor below that level is
        removed or non-walkable.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Both retail No Floor Event Points use <Bold>None</Bold>, which applies the no-floor effect as
        soon as the mission loads. Other trigger types like <Bold>Dependency</Bold> could be used if
        the floor should disappear at a scripted moment, but this is not observed in retail data.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Listening Mode
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Both retail No Floor examples use <Bold>Active</Bold>. This is appropriate for a permanent
        environmental change that should remain in effect once applied. Other listening modes are not
        needed unless the floor should dynamically toggle or disappear temporarily.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        No Floor-Specific Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        No Floor has <Bold>no type-specific Data settings</Bold>. The Event Point's behaviour is
        entirely determined by its presence and the common properties (position, trigger, listening
        mode). The mere existence of a No Floor Event Point in the mission is what activates the
        no-floor effect.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Authoring tip:</Run>
                <Run> No Floor is a presence-based Event Point with no configuration. Add it to the mission, place it centrally in the rooftop area, and use None/Active to activate it at mission start.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        How Missions Trigger No Floor
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Both retail No Floor Event Points use <Bold>None</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold>, meaning the
        no-floor effect is applied at mission start. Other plausible trigger patterns include:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>None</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold> - the observed retail pattern. The floor is removed as soon as the mission loads and remains absent for the entire mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Dependency</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold> - would remove the floor when another Event Point fires, useful if the floor should disappear at a scripted moment (for example, after an explosion or environmental event).</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Radius</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold> - would remove the floor when the player enters a specific area, though this is speculative and not observed in retail.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2" CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Important:</Run>
                <Run> No Floor is an extreme environmental change. Only use it when the mission is specifically designed for rooftop-only gameplay. Missions with No Floor must ensure players spawn on rooftops and that all objectives are reachable on rooftops.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#666" Margin="0,18,0,14"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Common No Floor Patterns
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">Rooftop Battle Environment At Mission Start</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>None</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold> when the entire mission should take place on
        rooftops with no walkable ground floor. This is the only observed retail pattern.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Observed example</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        In <Bold>Finale1.ucm</Bold> and <Bold>Finale1b.ucm</Bold>, No Floor Event Points <Bold>92</Bold>
        and <Bold>92</Bold> (respectively) are placed at position X: 12791, Y: 1792, Z: 9363. Both use
        trigger <Bold>None</Bold> with listening mode <Bold>Active</Bold>. When the mission loads, the
        ground floor is immediately removed, forcing all gameplay to take place on rooftops. These are
        finale missions where the player battles the final boss on rooftops above a missing floor.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">How to author it</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Add a <Bold>No Floor</Bold> Event Point to the mission. Place it centrally in the rooftop
        battle area. Set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>None</Bold> and listening mode to
        <Bold>Active</Bold>. Ensure the mission is designed so the player spawns on a rooftop and all
        mission objectives are accessible on rooftops without needing the ground floor.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">Scripted Floor Removal</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Dependency</Bold> with <Bold>Active</Bold> if the floor should disappear at a
        specific scripted moment rather than at mission start. This is not observed in retail but would
        be a plausible pattern for dramatic environmental changes.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Hypothetical example</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        A mission has an explosion or environmental event that destroys the ground floor mid-mission.
        The No Floor Event Point uses <Bold>Dependency</Bold> on the explosion Event Point, with
        listening mode <Bold>Active</Bold>. When the explosion fires, the ground floor disappears and
        players must stay on rooftops for the remainder of the mission.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">How to author it</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>Dependency</Bold> and <Bold>EP Ref</Bold> to the Event
        Point that should cause the floor to disappear. Use listening mode <Bold>Active</Bold> so the
        floor remains absent after the trigger fires.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">Extremely Rare Usage</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        No Floor is one of the rarest Event Point types in retail data. Only <Bold>2</Bold> instances
        exist across 76 retail missions, both in finale missions. This suggests No Floor is a
        special-purpose feature for very specific mission scenarios.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Observed pattern</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Of 16,259 Event Points across all retail missions, only <Bold>2</Bold> are No Floor. Both are
        in finale missions (<Bold>Finale1.ucm</Bold> and <Bold>Finale1b.ucm</Bold>), which are the
        final boss battles of the game. Both are placed at the exact same position and use the exact
        same trigger settings (None/Active).
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">How to apply</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Only use No Floor when the mission is specifically designed for rooftop-only gameplay. This is
        not a general-purpose feature — it is a dramatic environmental change that requires the entire
        mission to be built around the absence of the ground floor. Most missions do not need No Floor.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Basic No Floor Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the mission is designed for rooftop-only gameplay. No Floor is an extreme environmental change and should only be used in missions specifically built for it.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Ensure the mission has rooftop spawn points, rooftop objectives, and rooftop enemy placements. Players should never need the ground floor.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Add a <Bold>No Floor</Bold> Event Point to the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Place the Event Point centrally in the rooftop battle area or at a position that makes sense for the no-floor effect.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Y altitude</Bold> to rooftop height or the level below which the floor should be removed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>For mission-start no-floor (the standard pattern), set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>None</Bold> and listening mode to <Bold>Active</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>For scripted floor removal, set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>Dependency</Bold> or another trigger type and configure the appropriate trigger parameters.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test the mission in-game and confirm the floor is removed as expected, that players spawn on rooftops, and that all objectives are reachable without the ground floor.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Test falling behaviour to ensure NPCs and players who fall off rooftops behave as intended (death, respawn, etc.).</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2" CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final checklist:</Run>
                <Run> The mission is designed for rooftop-only gameplay, players spawn on rooftops, all objectives are accessible on rooftops, the No Floor Event Point is placed and triggered correctly, and falling behaviour is tested.</Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>
